Defendant in custody.   
John Vaughn sworn to interpret.   
Count 1 - 1st degree recklessly endangering safety - Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total sentence of fifty-four (54) months.   Eighteen (18) months initial confinement, followed by three (3) years extended supervision.   Conditions of extended supervision are:
1) No possession of any firearms;
2) Maintain absolute sobriety; 
3) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
4) No contact with the victim, Luis Gillen-Garcia;
5) Maintain full-time employment/job search combination;
6) Submit DNA sample;
7) Pay costs of action;
8) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.
Court finds the defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Substance Abuse Program.   
Defendant is given credit for 293 days time already served.   
Count 2 - Endanger safety with use of dangerous weapon - Defendant is sentenced to the Manitowoc County Jail for ninety (90) days, concurrent with Count 1, time served.  
Count 4 - Criminal damage to property - Defendant is sentenced to the Manitowoc County Jail for ninety (90) days, concurrent with Counts 1 & 2, time served.
Count 5 - Disorderly conduct with use of dangerous weapon - Defendant is sentenced to the Manitowoc County Jail for thirty (30) days, concurrent with Counts 1, 2, and 4, time served.  
Court costs are waived on counts 2, 4 and 5.  
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief. 
